div.p:
This Government has perfected its local organization. Proceeding under the
                    direction of the Executive Committee, in cooperation with the Secretary General,
                    a committee has been designated to invite preparation of papers on topics of
                    special interest and pertinent to the subject-matter of the nine program
                    sections. These sections are as follows: 
                        I.

Anthropology;
                        II.

Astronomy, Meteorology, and Seismology;
                        III.

Conservation of Natural Resources, Agriculture, Irrigation, and
                            Forestry;
                        IV.

Education;
                        V.

Engineering;
                        VI.

International Law, Public Law, and Jurisprudence;
                        VII.

Mining and Metallurgy, Economic Geology, and Applied Chemistry;
                        VIII.

Public Health and Medical Science;
                        IX.

Transportation, Commerce, Finance, and Taxation.
